                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12928058" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 23:12:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add in this too when I make test... this makes HBaseAdmin immune to odd .META. rows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12928134" author="stack" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2010 06:11:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as &apos;wont fix&apos;.  There are so many places in the code that presume a non-null regioninfo in .META. - - MetaScanner, MetaReader, AssignmentManager, CatalogJanitor, etc. &amp;#8211; that a test would be hard to write.  Would need to test w/ empty HRI during master joining cluster, during bulk startup, during &apos;normal&apos; operation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017501" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
